{"questionId":"29618829","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to form equation for the sum of frequencies<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math> or mean<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to eliminate one variable from their equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>48</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A0A0M0A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> with no working.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29618829","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.1a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of p and the value of q.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Prior learning","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}